    "Id": "chassisdef_vishnu_VSU-B",
    "Name": "Vishnu",
    "Details": "The Vishnu VSU-B is a 75-ton Arcturan Arms heavy BattleMech introduced in 3078, built around a symmetrical weapons layout that covers both long and close range without compromise. Two arm-mounted ER Large Lasers handle extended engagements, while four Streak SRM 4 launchers split evenly between the right and left torsos deliver guaranteed close-range damage on confirmed lock, fed by four CASE-protected tons of ammunition. Two center-torso Medium Lasers provide supplementary fire across the mid-range band.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Improved Targeting - Long</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.09</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Lower, Right Lower</color>",
    "Icon": "NEEDS_ICON"
