  "StockRole": "Brawler",
  "YangsThoughts": "Arcturan Arms was mostly keeping the lights on with RetroTech contracts during the Jihad, so the Vishnu stands out as evidence they had not completely walked away from advanced design work. The LCAF picked it up in serious numbers and kept running it into the Dark Age, deploying it heavily along the Jade Falcon and Free Worlds League borders where it had to perform against a wide range of opponents at unpredictable ranges. A heavy mech that stays dangerous whether the enemy closes or holds distance is exactly what a contested border unit wants.",
